original: Kaijser, Stig Otto Lorentz G:son, landsfogde, krigsfiskal, Karlskrona, f. 14/1/01 i Landskrona av kapt. Gustaf K. o. Ottonie Liljenstolpe. G. 34 m. Ingrid Maechel. Barn: Lorentz S:son f. 35, Elisabeth S:dotter 36, Magnus S :son 42. — Studrex. i Linköp. 21, jur. kand. i Upps. 26, polischef’sku’rs 35. Tingest jg. i Medels ta här. doms. 25-29, tf. boTigmiäst. i Roinneby, tf. brott-målsrådm. o. polismäst. i Kaxlskroina, tf. stadsfiskal där, bitr. länsnot. h. läns- styr. f. Bleik. 1. 29, tf. landsfogde 34, landsfogde sed. 36. Krigsfiskal v. Karlskr. örlogsstat. o. Karlskr. kustart: reg. sed’. 34. Allm. omb. i sparbanker i Blek 1. RNO.
translated: Kaijser, Stig Otto Lorentz G:son, county governor, war fiscal officer, Karlskrona, born on 14/1/01 in Landskrona to Captain Gustaf K. and Ottonie Liljenstolpe. Married in '34 to Ingrid Maechel. Children: Lorentz, born in '35, Elisabeth, born in '36, Magnus, born in '42. Studied at Linköping University until '21, graduated with a law degree from Uppsala University in '26, attended a police chief's course in '35. Worked as a magistrate in Medelsta District Court from '25 to '29, served as acting bailiff in Ronneby, acting judge and police chief in Karlskrona, acting city fiscal officer there, deputy county treasurer in Blekinge County Board from '29, acting county governor from '34, and county governor from '36. Serves as war fiscal officer for the Karlskrona naval station and the Karlskrona coastal artillery regiment since '34. Serves as general representative in savings banks in Blekinge County. Awarded the Royal Order of the North Star (RNO).

award.name: Royal Order of the North Star
